                     <p> ALLERTON (Hospital of St. James at). <persName>
                           <forename>Philip</forename>, bp.
                  of <placeName role="bishop" type="diocese" key="place_103020">Durham</placeName>
                        </persName>, grants to the 
                  <orgName key="org_103020">hospital of St. James, near Alverton</orgName>, in frankalmoigne, all his half of the mills of
                     <placeName key="place_103226">Houhton</placeName>, <placeName key="place_103317">Reningt<supplied>on</supplied>
                        </placeName> and
                     <placeName key="place_103380">Trolleforde</placeName>, after the death of <persName>master
                        <forename>Peter</forename> the <surname>Goldsmith</surname>
                        </persName> who
                  holds them for his life, subject to his paying one mark yearly to the Hospital. 
                  [<origDate when="1200" precision="low">c. 1200</origDate>.] 
                  <!--This seems to be online in Latin: https://deeds.library.utoronto.ca/charters/03280234
                  
                  English Episcopal Acta: Durham, 1196-1237 no. 234 says 'Trolleford' is unidentified
                  -->
                  . </p>
